1
00:00:26,160 --> 00:00:29,520
BANGKOK

2
00:00:30,360 --> 00:00:31,240
SWITZERLAND

3
00:00:40,040 --> 00:00:43,120
1997

4
00:01:44,240 --> 00:01:46,560
Love is the best thing in life.

5
00:01:47,640 --> 00:01:48,920
You're the only single one now.

6
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:50,680
It's time to get a girlfriend.

7
00:03:17,240 --> 00:03:18,120
Hey.

8
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:20,600
I think I saw someone following us.

9
00:03:24,880 --> 00:03:26,160
I can't see them now.

10
00:03:26,640 --> 00:03:27,800
Let's go.

11
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:30,880
Let's go.

12
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:41,960
- Hey, Cheewa. Look at the flowers.
- Yes.

13
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:46,680
- My gosh, they're beautiful.
- Yes.

14
00:03:46,760 --> 00:03:47,760
The colors are so pretty.

15
00:03:51,720 --> 00:03:53,720
- There should be more up ahead.
- Yes.

16
00:04:06,440 --> 00:04:07,800
What is it, Cheewan?

17
00:04:10,160 --> 00:04:11,680
It's nothing. Let's go.

18
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:32,400
Oh my gosh!

19
00:04:33,160 --> 00:04:34,920
- Cheewa. Let's take some photos.
- Yes.

20
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:42,240
One, two, three.

21
00:04:44,000 --> 00:04:45,040
Two, three.

22
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:47,600
Stand here.

23
00:04:47,680 --> 00:04:48,680
One, two.

24
00:05:08,240 --> 00:05:10,680
- The hill was so steep.
- Right. I'm so sore.

25
00:05:11,480 --> 00:05:12,480
Dara.

26
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:14,320
Dalad.

27
00:05:14,920 --> 00:05:16,040
You've arrived.

28
00:05:16,600 --> 00:05:19,600
Yes, I hopped on the train
right after work.

29
00:05:19,680 --> 00:05:21,240
I couldn't wait.

30
00:05:21,320 --> 00:05:23,960
I worked hard to save up for this trip.

31
00:05:24,040 --> 00:05:26,040
Cheewan, have something to eat.

32
00:05:26,120 --> 00:05:26,960
Okay.

33
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:29,200
Do you want a sandwich?

34
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:32,240
How do you like it?

35
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:36,320
It's okay. Cheewan will prepare it for me.

36
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:38,280
Excuse me.

37
00:05:49,200 --> 00:05:51,400
She has her own personal maid.

38
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:53,440
She doesn't need us.

39
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:56,440
Ms. Poncheewa is the daughter
of a gold shop owner.

40
00:05:56,520 --> 00:05:58,800
She won't talk
to poor Thai students like us.

41
00:06:00,320 --> 00:06:02,640
Hey, it's not like that.

42
00:06:03,360 --> 00:06:05,320
She's just picky about food

43
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:07,200
and she isn't good at socializing.

44
00:06:07,280 --> 00:06:09,720
Don't think too much.
You'll get to know her soon.

45
00:06:11,080 --> 00:06:12,280
You're not like her, are you?

46
00:06:14,840 --> 00:06:16,520
I'm just a poor, silly girl.

47
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:19,040
With my plain looks, I'm no match for her.

48
00:06:23,080 --> 00:06:23,960
Who is it?

49
00:06:28,120 --> 00:06:29,440
There's no one there.

50
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:31,000
I wonder who it was.

51
00:06:31,080 --> 00:06:33,080
Why are they being so sneaky?

52
00:06:44,840 --> 00:06:48,640
There's a story about this hotel.

53
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:51,280
A country girl

54
00:06:51,360 --> 00:06:55,200
was sent to marry a rich man
who owned this hotel.

55
00:06:55,280 --> 00:06:57,440
Are there such stories as this
in Europe too?

56
00:06:57,520 --> 00:07:01,240
But then the rich man fell in love
with a high-class woman

57
00:07:01,320 --> 00:07:02,640
and didn't marry the country girl.

58
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:05,320
The country girl was outraged

59
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:07,720
to be shunned by him.

60
00:07:07,800 --> 00:07:10,760
She had an elder brother,

61
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:12,600
but he had passed away.

62
00:07:12,680 --> 00:07:13,600
- What?
- What?

63
00:07:14,240 --> 00:07:16,240
She believed her brother's spirit

64
00:07:16,320 --> 00:07:18,080
protected her,

65
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:20,400
so she performed a voodoo ceremony

66
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:22,840
to summon his spirit.

67
00:07:24,040 --> 00:07:26,000
So Westerners also do black magic.

68
00:07:26,480 --> 00:07:28,640
- Was she able to summon him?
- Yes.

69
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:33,600
The brother then haunted
the rich man and his wife

70
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:36,600
until they could no longer handle it
and they died.

71
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:38,480
They say

72
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:43,360
the spirit is still

73
00:07:43,440 --> 00:07:45,920
in the basement of this hotel!

74
00:07:47,440 --> 00:07:49,560
Then one fine day,

75
00:07:49,640 --> 00:07:52,960
someone saw the shadow of a man

76
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:55,600
and heard someone clearing his throat.

77
00:07:59,520 --> 00:08:01,760
Stop it, Dalad.

78
00:08:01,840 --> 00:08:03,840
What? It wasn't me.

79
00:08:04,880 --> 00:08:06,880
What? Who was it then?

80
00:08:06,960 --> 00:08:08,480
I don't know.

81
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:14,520
Hey, Venus, did you book us
into a haunted hotel?

82
00:08:18,800 --> 00:08:20,920
- It's a ghost!
- My gosh, a ghost!

83
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:24,480
Cheewan!

84
00:08:24,560 --> 00:08:26,160
Where are you? I can't see you.

85
00:08:26,240 --> 00:08:27,560
Cheewan!

86
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:31,640
Cheewan!

87
00:08:35,919 --> 00:08:37,240
It's a ghost!

88
00:08:41,919 --> 00:08:43,960
- It's a ghost!
- A ghost?

89
00:08:50,280 --> 00:08:51,240
- Enough!
- Enough!

90
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:55,880
Come on, I'm scared of ghosts.

91
00:08:59,040 --> 00:09:00,040
Hold on, Mod.

92
00:09:00,120 --> 00:09:00,960
What?

93
00:09:01,040 --> 00:09:02,440
Why are you here?

94
00:09:10,280 --> 00:09:11,320
Nat.

95
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:12,720
Let go of me.

96
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:14,720
Why are you so pretty?

97
00:09:14,800 --> 00:09:16,000
Let go of me.

98
00:09:16,520 --> 00:09:18,760
So it wasn't a ghost sneaking around,

99
00:09:18,840 --> 00:09:20,080
it was you.

100
00:09:20,160 --> 00:09:21,680
I just got here.

101
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:24,560
I came because I miss you so badly.

102
00:09:24,640 --> 00:09:26,600
Let go of me, Nat.

103
00:09:26,680 --> 00:09:28,520
Let go. Help!

104
00:09:28,600 --> 00:09:29,480
Help!

105
00:09:29,560 --> 00:09:31,520
- Get your hands off her!
- Gosh!

106
00:09:35,560 --> 00:09:38,560
Dalad, how dare you punch me?

107
00:09:38,640 --> 00:09:41,080
There are so many ways to woo a woman.

108
00:09:41,160 --> 00:09:42,680
This isn't one of them.

109
00:09:42,760 --> 00:09:44,800
Before you lecture me,

110
00:09:44,880 --> 00:09:46,840
can you afford to pay your tuition fees?

111
00:09:47,920 --> 00:09:49,040
You loser.

112
00:09:49,120 --> 00:09:50,200
Hey.

113
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:52,280
Why are you talking to him like that?

114
00:09:53,880 --> 00:09:54,920
Hey.

115
00:09:57,040 --> 00:09:57,880
Hey.

116
00:10:00,160 --> 00:10:03,440
I'll pay both of your tuition fees,

117
00:10:03,520 --> 00:10:06,560
but you must bow down to me first.

118
00:10:06,640 --> 00:10:08,080
Bow down to you?

119
00:10:08,160 --> 00:10:10,040
- Hey.
- Dalad.

120
00:10:11,160 --> 00:10:12,320
Nat.

121
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:15,440
Haven't you been paying Cheewan
to clean your house?

122
00:10:15,520 --> 00:10:16,840
That's right.

123
00:10:16,920 --> 00:10:19,040
She didn't have money to pay for her flat,

124
00:10:19,120 --> 00:10:21,440
so she asked me to hire her. Right?

125
00:10:21,520 --> 00:10:23,360
Yes, sir.

126
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:27,200
Cheewan has been to your place so often

127
00:10:27,280 --> 00:10:29,280
that she has discovered
many secrets about you.

128
00:10:29,360 --> 00:10:31,240
I wonder what those secrets are.

129
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,560
Those secrets?

130
00:10:34,640 --> 00:10:36,840
One day, I was vacuuming the floor

131
00:10:36,920 --> 00:10:40,800
and someone suddenly screamed
because he was scared of a creature.

132
00:10:40,880 --> 00:10:43,240
What happened again?

133
00:10:43,320 --> 00:10:44,440
Cheewan!

134
00:10:44,520 --> 00:10:46,400
Gosh, I'm dying to say it.

135
00:10:46,480 --> 00:10:50,000
Hey, do you want me to tell them
what you're scared of?

136
00:10:50,080 --> 00:10:51,760
Stop right there.

137
00:10:52,320 --> 00:10:55,360
Hold on.
Is there something Nat is scared of?

138
00:10:55,440 --> 00:10:57,800
I've known him for ages
and I don't even know that.

139
00:10:58,280 --> 00:10:59,520
What are you scared of?

140
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:01,760
Mod, do you want to get it?

141
00:11:02,600 --> 00:11:03,760
I'm sorry.

142
00:11:04,680 --> 00:11:06,560
If you don't want her to expose you,

143
00:11:06,640 --> 00:11:08,000
then leave

144
00:11:08,080 --> 00:11:09,360
and stop messing with me.

145
00:11:10,160 --> 00:11:11,560
Okay?

146
00:11:11,640 --> 00:11:12,840
Fine, I'll leave,

147
00:11:12,920 --> 00:11:14,840
but I need to pay for my room first.

148
00:11:14,920 --> 00:11:17,160
We still have time, Poncheewa.

149
00:11:18,440 --> 00:11:20,120
Mod, let's go.

150
00:11:20,200 --> 00:11:23,280
- Okay, but I still don't know what it is.
- Stop it.

151
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:24,280
Okay.

152
00:11:24,360 --> 00:11:25,560
Are you staying here?

153
00:11:25,640 --> 00:11:27,600
Who invited you?

154
00:11:31,720 --> 00:11:33,880
Gosh, the power is finally back.

155
00:11:34,520 --> 00:11:35,440
Let's go.

156
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:38,280
- Let's go.
- Let's go.

157
00:11:38,360 --> 00:11:39,880
Let's go, Cheewa.

158
00:11:39,960 --> 00:11:40,960
Okay.

159
00:11:42,520 --> 00:11:44,880
By the way, what is he scared of?

160
00:12:04,200 --> 00:12:05,840
Thank you for helping me.

161
00:12:05,920 --> 00:12:06,800
Sure.

162
00:12:08,160 --> 00:12:10,080
Nat is from a rich family.

163
00:12:10,640 --> 00:12:12,640
If you had punched him,

164
00:12:14,040 --> 00:12:15,960
life would be difficult for you here.

165
00:12:16,040 --> 00:12:19,120
So? Are you saying I was thoughtless?

166
00:12:19,720 --> 00:12:22,840
People like him
don't show their fear, ma'am.

167
00:12:26,520 --> 00:12:28,640
I'm warning you.
There's no need to be sarcastic.

168
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:32,320
Anyway, thank you.

169
00:12:37,720 --> 00:12:38,600
- Eleven.
- Eleven.

170
00:12:38,680 --> 00:12:40,840
Hey, you're so fast.

171
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:41,760
All right.

172
00:12:41,840 --> 00:12:43,920
- One, two, three, four,
- One, two, three, four,

173
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:45,520
- five, six, seven, eight,
- five, six, seven, eight,

174
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:47,200
- nine, ten, eleven.
- nine, ten, eleven.

175
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,880
- Are you buying it?
- One hundred.

176
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:50,880
My gosh.

177
00:12:55,320 --> 00:12:56,320
Hold on.

178
00:12:56,960 --> 00:13:00,040
Did any of you hear that?

179
00:13:00,120 --> 00:13:01,360
I did.

180
00:13:01,440 --> 00:13:02,640
Loud and clear.

181
00:13:08,520 --> 00:13:09,360
Cheewa.

182
00:13:10,880 --> 00:13:12,280
Do you want to join us?

183
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:18,120
No. I'm going to read a book.

184
00:13:19,960 --> 00:13:22,040
That's what smart people do.

185
00:13:22,120 --> 00:13:25,280
Hey, we're also smart.
We're doing some calculations here.

186
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:26,600
Let's continue.

187
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:30,280
- Shall we continue?
- Okay.

188
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,080
Hey.

189
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:36,480
Where is my purse?

190
00:13:37,640 --> 00:13:39,160
Is your purse missing?

191
00:13:39,240 --> 00:13:41,720
- Yes.
- Is it in the bag?

192
00:13:41,800 --> 00:13:43,440
No, it's not here.

193
00:13:44,080 --> 00:13:45,160
No.

194
00:13:45,240 --> 00:13:46,120
Let me see.

195
00:13:46,200 --> 00:13:47,680
There's nothing here.

196
00:13:50,200 --> 00:13:51,800
It's not the ghost's doing.

197
00:13:56,280 --> 00:13:57,520
Venus, come here.

198
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:05,040
On the count of three,

199
00:14:05,680 --> 00:14:07,000
you open the door.

200
00:14:07,080 --> 00:14:08,160
- Me?
- Yes.

201
00:14:08,840 --> 00:14:11,240
Come on, open the door
on the count of three.

202
00:14:11,320 --> 00:14:12,160
Okay.

203
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:24,200
One, two, three.

204
00:14:32,440 --> 00:14:33,720
What is this?

205
00:14:33,800 --> 00:14:34,960
- Let go of me.
- No.

206
00:14:35,040 --> 00:14:36,000
It's me.

207
00:14:37,320 --> 00:14:38,440
I'm your cousin.

208
00:14:38,520 --> 00:14:39,960
Don't pretend to be the ghost's cousin.

209
00:14:40,520 --> 00:14:42,280
You fooled us, you thief.

210
00:14:42,360 --> 00:14:44,200
Give my friend's purse back.

211
00:14:44,280 --> 00:14:46,000
- What purse?
- Where is it?

212
00:14:46,080 --> 00:14:48,240
- Give it back.
- What are you doing?

213
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:50,200
What is this?

214
00:14:52,920 --> 00:14:54,000
A flashlight.

215
00:14:57,480 --> 00:15:00,640
Tell me it's a flashlight.

216
00:15:00,720 --> 00:15:03,320
- My gosh.
- My gosh.

217
00:15:03,400 --> 00:15:07,200
It must be a big one
because it's very dark here.

218
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:10,680
Go away, you brat.

219
00:15:11,280 --> 00:15:13,640
Hey, I found my purse.

220
00:15:15,000 --> 00:15:16,360
I found it.

221
00:15:16,440 --> 00:15:18,200
It was under the table.

222
00:15:18,280 --> 00:15:19,720
What?

223
00:15:19,800 --> 00:15:22,120
What? But the thief…

224
00:15:23,280 --> 00:15:25,040
Where did he go?

225
00:15:25,640 --> 00:15:27,080
That was fast.

226
00:15:28,360 --> 00:15:29,240
Who was he?

227
00:15:29,840 --> 00:15:31,440
He was Thai.

228
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:34,440
So was that a person

229
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:37,160
or a ghost?

230
00:15:54,200 --> 00:15:57,240
There's a letter for you from Thailand.

231
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:01,960
Thai people have very nice handwriting.

232
00:16:04,200 --> 00:16:05,040
Thank you.

233
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:26,520
My dear Cheewan,

234
00:16:26,600 --> 00:16:29,520
Saruj has assumed his duty

235
00:16:29,600 --> 00:16:33,240
as the first secretary in that country.

236
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:35,400
He must have arrived by now.

237
00:16:35,480 --> 00:16:37,560
Is Mr. Saruj working here?

238
00:16:52,440 --> 00:16:56,520
All of his cousins have married.

239
00:16:56,600 --> 00:17:00,200
I can't help but worry about him.

240
00:17:00,280 --> 00:17:03,880
Having considered it, I think Poncheewa,

241
00:17:03,960 --> 00:17:08,520
Kedsara's daughter,
is the most suitable for him.

242
00:17:09,079 --> 00:17:14,079
Kedsara is like family to us Jutatheps.

243
00:17:14,160 --> 00:17:15,599
If we can make a bond with her,

244
00:17:15,680 --> 00:17:19,560
she'll really become our family.

245
00:17:20,040 --> 00:17:23,359
If you love and respect me,

246
00:17:23,440 --> 00:17:27,920
I hope you will do exactly as I say.

247
00:17:28,520 --> 00:17:29,880
First.

248
00:17:32,160 --> 00:17:34,160
Do everything you can

249
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:37,360
to make sure
Saruj falls in love with Poncheewa.

250
00:17:37,880 --> 00:17:42,480
Second, don't tell anyone about this.

251
00:17:44,600 --> 00:17:47,560
Make Mr. Saruj fall in love with Cheewa?

252
00:17:51,120 --> 00:17:52,560
Mr. Saruj.

253
00:17:53,880 --> 00:17:55,440
Poncheewa.

254
00:17:57,560 --> 00:17:59,960
That would be a good match.

255
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:03,080
Now, I have something fun to do.

256
00:18:13,400 --> 00:18:16,760
Leave this to me, Madam Orn.

257
00:18:23,480 --> 00:18:24,840
Hey,

258
00:18:24,920 --> 00:18:25,920
come here.

259
00:18:29,200 --> 00:18:30,560
Here.

260
00:18:32,400 --> 00:18:36,880
Daeng said they must be important Thai
customers as the embassy staff are coming.

261
00:18:36,960 --> 00:18:38,640
They've booked out the whole restaurant

262
00:18:39,120 --> 00:18:42,400
and they will pay you double.

263
00:18:43,880 --> 00:18:45,680
- To do a traditional dance?
- Yes.

264
00:18:46,640 --> 00:18:48,840
What kind of Thai dance?

265
00:18:49,560 --> 00:18:51,360
Daeng said you could do what you like.

266
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:52,960
It's a birthday party.

267
00:18:54,840 --> 00:18:56,240
Fine, I'll do it.

268
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:00,600
What about a costume?

269
00:19:01,480 --> 00:19:03,000
It's being delivered.

270
00:19:05,880 --> 00:19:07,280
- Let's go.
- Okay.

271
00:19:09,320 --> 00:19:12,520
- Hey, let's make a toast to Nat.
- Come on.

272
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:14,320
Feel free to order more.

273
00:19:20,120 --> 00:19:22,040
- Hey, you're here.
- Hey, Nat.

274
00:19:22,120 --> 00:19:23,160
Nat.

275
00:19:23,240 --> 00:19:26,200
Didn't anyone tell you
the whole restaurant is booked?

276
00:19:26,280 --> 00:19:28,320
Someone is throwing a birthday party.

277
00:19:28,920 --> 00:19:30,480
I'm that someone.

278
00:19:30,560 --> 00:19:32,880
Today is my birthday.

279
00:19:39,320 --> 00:19:41,480
Are you the one hiring me to dance?

280
00:19:41,560 --> 00:19:42,680
That's right.

281
00:19:43,160 --> 00:19:46,760
I want you to wish me a happy birthday,

282
00:19:46,840 --> 00:19:50,400
so I'll feel like I'm in heaven with you.

283
00:20:01,760 --> 00:20:03,440
It'll be tough today.

284
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:05,560
Let's get changed.

285
00:20:05,640 --> 00:20:09,040
Guys, someone else is joining us today.

286
00:20:09,120 --> 00:20:10,880
Please give a round of applause

287
00:20:10,960 --> 00:20:14,040
to the new first secretary
of the Royal Thai Embassy,

288
00:20:14,120 --> 00:20:18,160
M.L. Saruj Jutathep.

289
00:20:26,480 --> 00:20:28,120
Clap your hands.

290
00:20:28,200 --> 00:20:29,160
Hey.

291
00:20:37,440 --> 00:20:39,040
You said he was handsome,

292
00:20:39,120 --> 00:20:42,880
but you didn't say he was this handsome.

293
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:45,400
That's…

294
00:20:46,440 --> 00:20:47,560
It's me.

295
00:20:48,280 --> 00:20:49,720
Don't pretend to be the ghost's cousin.

296
00:20:49,800 --> 00:20:51,640
Give my friend's purse back.

297
00:20:53,920 --> 00:20:54,760
A flashlight.

298
00:20:58,560 --> 00:21:00,360
Who invited him?

299
00:21:00,440 --> 00:21:02,200
It's my duty, Mr. Natsarid.

300
00:21:02,280 --> 00:21:04,840
I have a duty to take care
of Thai students here.

301
00:21:06,280 --> 00:21:08,240
This is Venus, my daughter.

302
00:21:08,320 --> 00:21:09,720
Hello.

303
00:21:10,680 --> 00:21:11,840
I know who you are.

304
00:21:14,120 --> 00:21:15,120
Dara.

305
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:17,280
Dalad.

306
00:21:18,960 --> 00:21:20,440
Poncheewa.

307
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:25,520
Where's the other one?

308
00:21:27,320 --> 00:21:30,000
Cheewan.

309
00:21:31,080 --> 00:21:33,600
Do you remember Aunt Kratin's daughter?

310
00:21:38,760 --> 00:21:40,520
Hello.

311
00:21:41,080 --> 00:21:44,560
So how do you know us?

312
00:21:47,480 --> 00:21:49,120
- The ghost!
- The ghost!

313
00:21:51,360 --> 00:21:54,800
Did you follow us
to the mountain the other day?

314
00:21:58,240 --> 00:22:00,200
That's the best way

315
00:22:00,920 --> 00:22:02,920
to find out what you're up to.

316
00:22:09,320 --> 00:22:11,600
So I can report
to your parents how you are.

317
00:22:53,520 --> 00:22:55,480
You're still mad at me, aren't you?

318
00:22:59,240 --> 00:23:02,360
I'm sorry
for kicking you and touching your…

319
00:23:06,360 --> 00:23:08,840
I see. You don't want to talk about it.

320
00:23:08,920 --> 00:23:11,760
Okay, I won't mention it.

321
00:23:20,240 --> 00:23:21,800
I'm scared of you now.

322
00:23:28,160 --> 00:23:30,400
Mr. Saruj,

323
00:23:30,480 --> 00:23:33,080
Venus is taking a language course here.

324
00:23:33,160 --> 00:23:36,640
