455
00:35:44,600 --> 00:35:46,840
You ask him. Do it.

456
00:35:53,080 --> 00:35:54,480
You studied in England before,

457
00:35:54,560 --> 00:35:56,480
so you must have come here, right?

458
00:35:57,400 --> 00:35:58,280
Yes.

459
00:36:04,800 --> 00:36:07,760
Don't you have anything else to say?

460
00:36:09,960 --> 00:36:13,720
This country is where my parents met
and fell in love.

461
00:36:13,800 --> 00:36:15,600
Gosh.

462
00:36:15,680 --> 00:36:17,000
Please tell us about it.

463
00:36:20,560 --> 00:36:22,400
You must have heard about it.

464
00:36:22,480 --> 00:36:25,040
It's a well-known Jutathep story.

465
00:36:26,640 --> 00:36:30,120
Princess Wanrasa disguised herself
as a commoner

466
00:36:30,200 --> 00:36:32,880
and fell in love with M.R. Pavornruj
during her visit.

467
00:36:33,840 --> 00:36:34,760
Yes.

468
00:36:37,400 --> 00:36:39,640
Is that it?

469
00:36:46,280 --> 00:36:48,360
Aren't you going to ask him anything else?

470
00:36:59,120 --> 00:37:00,840
Madam Orn,

471
00:37:00,920 --> 00:37:03,240
they're like two peas in a pod.

472
00:37:03,800 --> 00:37:08,440
Can two shy people get together?

473
00:37:08,520 --> 00:37:10,640
I'm not sure about this at all.

474
00:37:10,720 --> 00:37:12,840
I've never had a husband.

475
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:14,560
Oh dear.

476
00:37:20,640 --> 00:37:21,640
- Cheewa.
- Yes?

477
00:37:21,720 --> 00:37:23,160
Give this to Mr. Saruj.

478
00:37:25,240 --> 00:37:26,400
Here you go, Saruj.

479
00:37:27,880 --> 00:37:29,160
