the Thai students to Jungfraujoch.

547
00:42:36,680 --> 00:42:40,080
Gosh, Saruj will take us on a trip.

548
00:42:40,160 --> 00:42:42,880
- My gosh.
- That's awesome.

549
00:43:19,000 --> 00:43:21,320
CHEEWAN

550
00:44:03,160 --> 00:44:04,680
It's so pretty.

551
00:44:10,520 --> 00:44:12,480
Hey, Cheewa.

552
00:44:12,560 --> 00:44:14,840
- Are you okay?
- I'm good. I just tripped on something.

553
00:44:44,920 --> 00:44:46,760
That's Mr. Saruj.

554
00:44:46,840 --> 00:44:48,760
This is Poncheewa.

555
00:44:56,920 --> 00:44:58,600
It's looking great.

556
00:45:14,240 --> 00:45:15,760
What are you doing?

557
00:45:19,840 --> 00:45:22,320
Well, it's nothing.

558
00:45:22,800 --> 00:45:24,200
But…

559
00:45:26,120 --> 00:45:27,640
they're cute, aren't they?

560
00:45:31,120 --> 00:45:35,160
Poncheewa is a good girl
and a good student.

561
00:45:35,240 --> 00:45:39,200
She's very prim and elegant.

562
00:45:39,280 --> 00:45:42,480
If you'd consider her

563
00:45:42,560 --> 00:45:44,920
to be your partner,

564
00:45:45,000 --> 00:45:47,800
then I'd be very happy.

565
00:45:47,880 --> 00:45:49,800
Although many Jutatheps

566
00:45:49,880 --> 00:45:53,640
have married Dhevaproms,

567
00:45:53,720 --> 00:45:55,600
I'd still like you

568
00:45:55,680 --> 00:45:59,400
to marry Kedsara's daughter,

569
00:45:59,480 --> 00:46:03,400
who is our beloved one.

570
00:46:03,880 --> 00:46:06,240
I miss and love you.

571
00:46:06,320 --> 00:46:08,080
Great-Grandma Orn.

572
00:46:28,080 --> 00:46:29,240
Let's dance, Cheewa.

573
00:46:58,560 --> 00:47:00,960
Do you have any information about tattoos?

574
00:47:01,040 --> 00:47:03,680
Gang tattoos, that sort of thing.

575
00:47:03,760 --> 00:47:04,640
Okay.

576
00:47:14,880 --> 00:47:15,800
What are you doing?

577
00:47:24,880 --> 00:47:27,640
What the hell are you doing? That hurts.

578
00:47:30,480 --> 00:47:32,040
What's going on, Mr. Saruj?

579
00:47:34,760 --> 00:47:36,720
He was putting drugs in the drink.

580
00:47:36,800 --> 00:47:38,160
Has anyone drunk it?

581
00:47:39,200 --> 00:47:40,880
Do you mean the punch?

582
00:47:42,080 --> 00:47:44,360
All of us drank it.

583
00:47:45,800 --> 00:47:48,360
Only the girls had it.
I was drinking beer.

584
00:47:50,440 --> 00:47:51,920
What the hell are you talking about?

585
00:47:52,680 --> 00:47:54,320
What drugs?

586
00:47:55,000 --> 00:47:58,000
This is caramel sugar that I made.

587
00:48:01,160 --> 00:48:03,160
Those foreigners are drug dealers.

588
00:48:03,720 --> 00:48:05,560
I saw you got it from them.

589
00:48:05,640 --> 00:48:07,640
You don't have any evidence,

590
00:48:07,720 --> 00:48:09,760
but you're already accusing me.

591
00:48:09,840 --> 00:48:11,400
I don't want anything from you,

592
00:48:11,480 --> 00:48:13,360
but let me throw a punch at you.

593
00:48:13,840 --> 00:48:15,240
- Hey!
- My gosh!

594
00:48:16,360 --> 00:48:18,280
If I take you for a urine test,

595
00:48:19,080 --> 00:48:20,560
do you think you'd pass it?

596
00:48:26,560 --> 00:48:30,080
I'll let it go this time.

597
00:48:30,160 --> 00:48:32,120
Make sure you leave me alone from now on.

598
00:48:42,480 --> 00:48:44,200
Did you drink a lot?

599
00:48:44,280 --> 00:48:48,000
No, I shared it with Simon and Dalad.

600
00:48:48,480 --> 00:48:50,320
I had three glasses

601
00:48:50,400 --> 00:48:52,000
because it was so good.

602
00:48:52,080 --> 00:48:54,040
How are you feeling now?

603
00:48:54,120 --> 00:48:55,600
I'm fine.

604
00:48:55,680 --> 00:48:57,280
He was targeting Poncheewa.

605
00:48:57,840 --> 00:48:59,120
But don't worry.

606
00:48:59,200 --> 00:49:01,000
I won't sleep tonight.

607
00:49:01,080 --> 00:49:03,040
You two take the bed.

608
00:49:05,080 --> 00:49:06,600
Tell me right away

609
00:49:06,680 --> 00:49:08,040
if you don't feel well.

610
00:49:09,520 --> 00:49:10,760
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

611
00:49:10,840 --> 00:49:11,720
It's fine.

612
00:49:12,920 --> 00:49:13,960
You should go to bed.

613
00:49:37,040 --> 00:49:39,600
By the way, Cheewan, Nat…

614
00:49:41,120 --> 00:49:42,520
Are you already asleep?

615
00:49:45,480 --> 00:49:47,080
That was quick.

616
00:49:51,400 --> 00:49:52,920
You can't sleep?

617
00:49:54,360 --> 00:49:55,360
No.

618
00:50:04,560 --> 00:50:06,360
What are you reading?

619
00:50:22,280 --> 00:50:23,360
Just sit down.

620
00:50:24,840 --> 00:50:26,600
Are you feeling dizzy?

621
00:50:26,680 --> 00:50:28,960
Tell me how you feel.

622
00:50:29,440 --> 00:50:32,400
It's nothing. I'm fine.

623
00:50:32,480 --> 00:50:35,400
I just tripped over the rug. I'm clumsy.

624
00:50:37,160 --> 00:50:38,520
Are you sure you're okay?

625
00:50:38,600 --> 00:50:39,560
Yes.

626
00:50:47,120 --> 00:50:49,400
I've read that book.

627
00:50:51,080 --> 00:50:52,800
Oh, right.

628
00:50:52,880 --> 00:50:55,240
I forgot you're a bookworm.

629
00:50:57,360 --> 00:50:59,520
There are many exciting parts.

630
00:50:59,600 --> 00:51:01,160
The war got me thinking

631
00:51:01,720 --> 00:51:05,240
that people's misguided beliefs
can cause the most pain and suffering.

632
00:51:05,320 --> 00:51:09,280
You think deeply for someone so young.

633
00:51:12,480 --> 00:51:14,520
Which part do you like?

634
00:51:15,680 --> 00:51:17,120
I like the whole book.

635
00:51:18,520 --> 00:51:22,640
When I was 13 like Anne Frank,
all I did was play with Lego.

636
00:51:28,320 --> 00:51:30,680
Have you ever visited her house?

637
00:51:30,760 --> 00:51:31,640
Yes.

638
00:51:32,600 --> 00:51:35,080
- I really want to go there.
- Really?

639
00:51:35,160 --> 00:51:37,040
- Yes.
- Sure.

640
00:51:37,120 --> 00:51:38,920
I'll take you when I have the chance.

641
00:51:39,000 --> 00:51:40,560
- Promise?
- Promise.

642
00:51:41,840 --> 00:51:43,400
You're so kind to me.

643
00:51:45,640 --> 00:51:47,640
Oh my gosh.

644
00:51:47,720 --> 00:51:52,040
Madam Orn, they finally found
something in common.

645
00:51:52,120 --> 00:51:54,080
There is hope for them.

646
00:51:54,160 --> 00:51:57,000
Oh my, they'll make such a good couple.

647
00:51:58,440 --> 00:52:02,960
I really hope Mr. Saruj will get
together with Poncheewa.

648
00:52:10,520 --> 00:52:13,240
I have an announcement to make.

649
00:52:13,320 --> 00:52:16,360
Cheewa got herself a boyfriend.

650
00:52:17,640 --> 00:52:19,400
- Cheewan, I don't--
- Hey.

651
00:52:20,160 --> 00:52:23,160
The guy is a distant relative.

652
00:52:23,240 --> 00:52:25,880
He came to work here

653
00:52:25,960 --> 00:52:28,320
in order to find his love.

654
00:52:29,240 --> 00:52:31,560
And that man is

655
00:52:32,280 --> 00:52:35,640
Mr. Saruj!

656
00:52:44,920 --> 00:52:47,240
I won't lose to you.

657
00:53:20,520 --> 00:53:22,800
Cheewan, wait up.

658
00:53:23,600 --> 00:53:27,320
Why did you say that?
Saruj and I aren't together.

659
00:53:31,160 --> 00:53:33,040
You should have asked me
before you said that.

660
00:53:33,120 --> 00:53:37,600
I did think of asking you for advice.

661
00:53:37,680 --> 00:53:39,840
Asking for advice means
you must ask me first,

662
00:53:39,920 --> 00:53:42,720
but you're telling me this afterward.
It's called informing.

663
00:53:42,800 --> 00:53:45,960
Poncheewa is a woman.
This might damage her reputation.

664
00:53:46,040 --> 00:53:48,640
Natsarid seemed serious about Cheewa.

665
00:53:48,720 --> 00:53:51,160
He's such a thug.

666
00:53:51,240 --> 00:53:54,720
But he was stunned
when I said you were after Cheewa.

667
00:53:57,800 --> 00:54:00,400
Did you do it to protect Poncheewa?

668
00:54:00,480 --> 00:54:01,480
Yes.

669
00:54:01,960 --> 00:54:04,040
I was killing two birds with one stone.

670
00:54:04,120 --> 00:54:05,440
What stone?

671
00:54:05,520 --> 00:54:06,640
What birds?

672
00:54:07,320 --> 00:54:10,280
Listen, please don't take it seriously.

673
00:54:10,760 --> 00:54:14,400
You're both single, aren't you?

674
00:54:18,440 --> 00:54:20,840
Then this won't be a problem.

675
00:54:20,920 --> 00:54:23,040
Just tell everyone this for now

676
00:54:23,120 --> 00:54:24,960
and keep it a secret between us.

677
00:54:28,160 --> 00:54:30,960
You could try dating if you like.

678
00:54:31,040 --> 00:54:31,960
What?

679
00:54:32,040 --> 00:54:34,120
- Hold on.
- Hey.

680
00:54:34,200 --> 00:54:36,280
You don't have to date.

681
00:54:36,360 --> 00:54:38,320
Let's just wait

682
00:54:38,400 --> 00:54:40,400
until Nat stops pursuing Cheewa

683
00:54:40,480 --> 00:54:42,160
and sets his sights on someone else.

684
00:54:42,800 --> 00:54:45,560
After that, we can tell everyone
that you two have broken up.

685
00:54:46,640 --> 00:54:49,240
Are you fine with this?

686
00:55:28,760 --> 00:55:29,680
Dalad.

687
00:55:30,440 --> 00:55:31,880
What are you doing here?

688
00:55:31,960 --> 00:55:33,600
This is the university cafe.

689
00:55:34,280 --> 00:55:35,480
I got a part-time job here.

690
00:55:35,960 --> 00:55:38,600
I couldn't afford to study
at a university like this.

691
00:55:39,880 --> 00:55:41,400
That's great. I can talk to you.

692
00:55:41,960 --> 00:55:44,320
I'm the only Thai student here.

693
00:55:44,400 --> 00:55:45,560
I'm a waiter.

694
00:55:45,640 --> 00:55:48,600
I can't just sit and chat with a customer.

695
00:55:49,760 --> 00:55:51,200
What can I get for you?

696
00:55:53,160 --> 00:55:54,800
Hi, Dalad.

697
00:55:54,880 --> 00:55:56,480
How is your first day at work?

698
00:55:56,560 --> 00:55:57,960
It's okay.

699
00:55:58,040 --> 00:55:59,800
- Cheewan, do you work here too?
- Yes?

700
00:56:00,480 --> 00:56:02,320
They only wanted a guy,

701
00:56:02,400 --> 00:56:05,160
so Dara and I have to stay
at the Thai restaurant.

702
00:56:05,240 --> 00:56:06,760
I see.

703
00:56:07,240 --> 00:56:08,640
How is it? Are you tired?

704
00:56:08,720 --> 00:56:09,800
Just a bit.

705
00:56:10,440 --> 00:56:11,720
Work hard.

706
00:56:13,560 --> 00:56:15,160
Is Mr. Saruj here yet?

707
00:56:17,440 --> 00:56:19,080
I got so many visitors today.

708
00:56:19,160 --> 00:56:21,320
I'm usually alone here.

709
00:56:24,160 --> 00:56:27,520
How could you be lonely?
You have a boyfriend, don't you?

710
00:56:28,480 --> 00:56:32,600
Hey, are you really dating him?

711
00:56:32,680 --> 00:56:35,280
I came here to find out about this.

712
00:56:51,800 --> 00:56:53,920
Here he is. Poncheewa's boyfriend is here.

713
00:57:00,600 --> 00:57:01,760
Come here.

714
00:57:03,720 --> 00:57:04,840
Mr. Saruj.

715
00:57:04,920 --> 00:57:07,840
Are you really dating Poncheewa?

716
00:57:11,560 --> 00:57:13,000
Poncheewa.

717
00:57:14,680 --> 00:57:16,000
I brought you some flowers.

718
00:57:17,240 --> 00:57:18,480
Take them.

719
00:57:20,360 --> 00:57:22,200
Gosh, the flowers are so pretty.

720
00:57:22,280 --> 00:57:24,000
Why don't you take them?

721
00:57:31,560 --> 00:57:33,840
You're asking for trouble.

722
00:57:34,520 --> 00:57:36,840
You reported it to my dad

723
00:57:36,920 --> 00:57:40,360
and he gave me an earful.

724
00:57:40,440 --> 00:57:43,080
I called your dad and told him that

725
00:57:43,160 --> 00:57:47,280
two of your friends were arrested
for drug possession.

726
00:57:50,080 --> 00:57:51,160
Bob.

727
00:57:51,240 --> 00:57:53,200
Did Bob get busted?

728
00:57:56,440 --> 00:57:59,920
Is he the guy who visited us at Jungfrau?

729
00:58:00,000 --> 00:58:01,560
All of Bob's friends have been arrested.

730
00:58:01,640 --> 00:58:03,040
As for you two,

731
00:58:03,120 --> 00:58:05,360
the police are keeping an eye on you.

732
00:58:05,440 --> 00:58:08,240
If you start a fight,
they'll be all over you.

733
00:58:10,000 --> 00:58:12,840
I suggest you two leave.

734
00:58:16,240 --> 00:58:17,560
Let's go.

735
00:58:17,640 --> 00:58:19,880
I'm not going. I want some coffee.

736
00:58:20,920 --> 00:58:23,560
I just came here to see Poncheewa.
I'm not doing anything wrong.

737
00:58:31,600 --> 00:58:34,680
Gosh, Nat hangs out with drug dealers.

738
00:58:34,760 --> 00:58:37,680
Do you think he also takes drugs?

739
00:58:37,760 --> 00:58:40,000
Of course he does.

740
00:59:02,840 --> 00:59:03,960
Hey.

741
00:59:05,400 --> 00:59:08,840
How dare you reject me
in front of other people like that?

742
00:59:09,440 --> 00:59:11,040
Why are you still here?

743
00:59:11,680 --> 00:59:15,400
I want to know what's so great
about that asshole Saruj?

744
00:59:16,160 --> 00:59:18,440
Let me tell you something.

745
00:59:18,520 --> 00:59:21,120
The Jutathep era is over.

746
00:59:21,200 --> 00:59:25,720
Now, it's time for my dad
and our family to step up.

747
00:59:25,800 --> 00:59:30,040
Don't you know that outsiders
aren't allowed in here? Get out.

748
00:59:31,000 --> 00:59:33,200
You got together with him,
you can break up with him too.

749
00:59:33,280 --> 00:59:36,480
I'll make sure you lose interest in Saruj.

750
00:59:43,360 --> 00:59:45,400
Can we talk later?

751
00:59:45,480 --> 00:59:47,000
Stop playing so hard to get.

752
00:59:47,080 --> 00:59:48,400
Do you see that?

753
00:59:48,960 --> 00:59:50,360
It's my new car.

754
00:59:50,440 --> 00:59:52,600
Come for a ride with me.

755
00:59:52,680 --> 00:59:53,960
No.

756
00:59:55,880 --> 00:59:56,720
No!

757
00:59:56,800 --> 00:59:59,920
No! Let go of me.

758
01:00:02,320 --> 01:00:03,960
No one can hear you.

759
01:00:04,040 --> 01:00:04,880
Cheewa.

760
01:00:17,080 --> 01:00:19,440
Come here, Cheewa. Leave us alone.

761
01:00:21,960 --> 01:00:24,080
Stop right now.

762
01:00:25,840 --> 01:00:27,160
Move!

763
01:00:28,240 --> 01:00:29,600
Do you think you're tough?

764
01:00:31,440 --> 01:00:34,200
- Stop it, Nat!
- Move!

765
01:00:36,480 --> 01:00:37,640
Dalad.

766
01:00:39,520 --> 01:00:40,840
You're tough, aren't you?

767
01:00:40,920 --> 01:00:42,440
You're tough, aren't you?

768
01:00:44,280 --> 01:00:46,520
Do you want to help her?

769
01:01:36,120 --> 01:01:37,240
Cheewa.

770
01:02:07,920 --> 01:02:08,880
Cheewan,

771
01:02:08,960 --> 01:02:10,760
why didn't you tell me you were coming?

772
01:02:13,200 --> 01:02:15,760
I haven't seen you for a week. I miss you.

773
01:02:17,280 --> 01:02:18,240
Wait a second.

774
01:02:18,840 --> 01:02:19,680
Just wait outside.

775
01:02:19,760 --> 01:02:21,400
Why?

776
01:02:21,480 --> 01:02:23,040
Why can't I come in?

777
01:02:24,160 --> 01:02:25,720
Is there someone in there?

778
01:02:26,520 --> 01:02:29,280
No, I'm alone.

779
01:02:29,360 --> 01:02:31,680
I thought you said
your roommate had gone home?

780
01:02:33,640 --> 01:02:36,280
You must have a guest.

781
01:02:38,320 --> 01:02:39,320
I knew it.

782
01:02:39,400 --> 01:02:41,160
There are two glasses.

783
01:02:41,720 --> 01:02:42,960
Well?

784
01:02:43,960 --> 01:02:46,000
It's not that. It's just that I'm naked.

785
01:02:46,960 --> 01:02:48,600
Come on, Cheewa.

786
01:02:48,680 --> 01:02:52,000
We've seen each other naked
since we were kids. Don't be shy.

787
01:02:52,080 --> 01:02:53,760
Let me come in. It's cold out here.

788
01:02:53,840 --> 01:02:54,680
Cheewan.

789
01:02:54,760 --> 01:02:56,760
Wait outside for a second.

790
01:02:56,840 --> 01:02:59,160
Give me a second
and we can go and get some hot cocoa.

791
01:03:00,200 --> 01:03:02,080
- Just a second.
- But it's cold…

792
01:03:38,480 --> 01:03:41,280
Hello.

793
01:03:41,360 --> 01:03:43,200
You two can get on the cruise first.

794
01:03:43,280 --> 01:03:44,360
I'll wait over there.

795
01:03:44,440 --> 01:03:45,880
Just go.

796
01:03:45,960 --> 01:03:49,800
You're so cute when you smile and laugh.

797
01:03:49,880 --> 01:03:50,960
Do you mean it?

798
01:03:51,040 --> 01:03:52,400
Yes.

799
01:03:57,400 --> 01:03:58,400
What's going on?

800
01:03:58,480 --> 01:04:00,960
- Venus is doing an internship here.
- With me?

801
01:04:01,040 --> 01:04:04,120
Please make way for a human removal unit.

802
01:04:04,680 --> 01:04:07,240
Mr. Saruj, there is
a big problem in Thailand.

803
01:04:07,320 --> 01:04:09,200
The Thai baht will depreciate.

804
01:04:09,280 --> 01:04:12,080
This is the biggest economic crisis
of the country.

805
01:04:12,160 --> 01:04:15,280
Madam Orn can't sponsor me any longer.

806
01:04:15,360 --> 01:04:17,280
I think I'll have to return to Thailand.

807
01:04:17,360 --> 01:04:19,600
We'll have half of the world
separating us now.

808
01:04:19,680 --> 01:04:21,880
I don't know
when I'll get to see you again.

809
01:04:48,560 --> 01:04:53,560
Subtitle translation by: Tanida Itthiwat
